doc_summary_long: Home Affairs Minister Peter Dutton said he was exploring giving South Africa's white farmers access to fast-track visas on humanitarian grounds. Mr Dutton had earlier told reporters in Australia that South Africa's white farmers were 'persecuted' and 'need help from a civilised country like ours'. However, the BBC found in November that there is no statistical proof that white farmers were more likely to be murdered than black farmers.
doc_summary_short: Home Affairs Minister Peter Dutton said he was exploring giving South Africa's white farmers access to fast-track visas on humanitarian grounds.
doc_title: Australia considers visas for white South African farmers
